text: Gusevka () is a rural locality (a selo) in Maloyazovsky Selsoviet, Salavatsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 199 as of 2010. There are 3 streets. == Geography == It is located 5 km from Maloyaz, 5 km from Tatarsky Maloyaz. == References == Category:Rural localities in Salavatsky District
title: Gusevka
